Caterpillar, Merck share gains contribute to Dow's nearly 100-point jump

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is climbing Friday morning with shares of Caterpillar and Merck seeing positive gains for the price-weighted average. Shares of Caterpillar CAT, -3.19% and Merck MRK, -1.24% are contributing to the index's intraday rally, as the Dow DJIA, -2.29% was most recently trading 98 points higher (0.3%). Caterpillar's shares have gained $1.95 (1.3%) while those of Merck are up $1.16, or 1.3%, combining for a roughly 21-point boost for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are Pfizer PFE, -0.68%, Walgreens Boots WBA, -2.18%, and Verizon Communications Inc. VZ, -0.25%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the index equates to a 6.78-point swing.